---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions | FastClickTest.com"
  description="Terms and conditions for using FastClickTest.com — the free online click speed test. Read the rules for using our CPS test tool fairly and responsibly."
  currentPage="terms"
>
<div class="page">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <h1>Terms <span class="hi">&amp; Conditions</span></h1>
    <p>Last updated: January 2025 — Plain English, no legal jargon.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-content">

    <h2>Terms of Service</h2>
    <p>
      By accessing and using FastClickTest.com, you agree to these terms. If you disagree,
      please stop using the site. We've written these in plain English — no surprises.
    </p>

    <h3>1. Acceptable Use</h3>
    <p>
      FastClickTest provides free click speed testing tools for personal, non-commercial use.
      You may use the site to measure your genuine clicking speed, practice techniques, and
      compare scores. You may share your results on social media or with friends.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Prohibited Activities</h3>
    <p>
      You agree not to use automated scripts, macros, or bots to artificially inflate your CPS
      scores for the purpose of claiming false records. You agree not to attempt to hack,
      overload, or disrupt the service in any way. You agree not to scrape or copy site content
      for commercial purposes without written permission.
    </p>

    <h3>3. Intellectual Property</h3>
    <p>
      All content on FastClickTest.com — including design, code, text, and graphics — is the
      property of FastClickTest.com. You may not reproduce or redistribute it without permission.
      Your own score data is yours — we don't claim any rights over it.
    </p>

    <h3>4. Disclaimer of Warranties</h3>
    <p>
      The service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee the
      service will be uninterrupted or error-free. CPS measurements are accurate to the limits
      of your browser and hardware — minor variations between devices are normal and expected.
    </p>

    <h3>5. Health Disclaimer</h3>
    <p>
      Certain clicking techniques — especially jitter clicking — involve repetitive muscle
      tension that can cause discomfort or repetitive strain injury (RSI) if done excessively.
      Use these techniques at your own discretion. Take regular breaks, stop immediately if
      you feel pain or numbness, and consult a doctor if symptoms persist. FastClickTest is
      not liable for any physical discomfort or injury resulting from use of this tool.
    </p>

    <h3>6. Limitation of Liability</h3>
    <p>
      FastClickTest shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages
      arising from your use of this service. Our total liability, if any, is limited to the amount
      you paid to use the service — which is zero, since it's free.
    </p>

    <h3>7. Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>
      We use Google Analytics and Google AdSense. Your use of this site is also subject to
      Google's Terms of Service. We are not responsible for third-party content or services.
    </p>

    <h3>8. Changes to Terms</h3>
    <p>
      We may update these terms at any time. The date above reflects the latest revision.
      Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h3>9. Contact</h3>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms? Use our <a href="/contact">contact page</a> to reach us.
    </p>

  </div>

</div>
</Layout>
